noria:OperationPlan_AppServerCPUOptimization dcterms:description "Procedure to identify and mitigate high CPU usage on application servers, involving process analysis, code review, resource scaling, and database query optimization."@en .

# Add more relations for anomaly patterns
noria:AnomalyPattern_NetworkLinkFlap dcterms:description "Pattern indicating a network link repeatedly going up and down, often due to faulty cabling or transceiver. This can cause intermittent connectivity issues and service disruptions, leading to user complaints."@en .
noria:AnomalyPattern_HighCPUApplicationImpact dcterms:description "Pattern where sustained high CPU on an application server correlates with degraded application performance, leading to slow response times and potential timeouts for end-users. Requires immediate investigation."@en .

# Add more relations for document attachments
noria:DocumentAttachment_NetworkDiagram_PDC dcterms:description "Detailed network diagram of the Paris Data Center, including physical and logical layouts, VLANs, IP subnets, and device interconnections. Essential for network troubleshooting and planning."@en .
noria:DocumentAttachment_ServerLog_TT002 dcterms:description "Compressed log file from app01.ny.example.com related to performance issue, containing application logs, system logs, and performance metrics collected during the incident period."@en .

